Honored that my song #missinyou has connected with so many people. It’s gone viral a few times now. Made me want to share the story of how before we released it I had second thoughts.. because of how personal it was to me. I wasn’t sure if that meant that no one would connect with it. I think the lesson for me was how similar all our lives actually are. We’re all going through the same stories, similar struggles differently but together. Sending love out today. thanks for sharing or saving this if you’ve ever connected with it 🍻 Still missin you, Pap

Writing this to try to begin the healing process. I honestly haven’t been able to come close to wrapping my head around the Nashville shooting. But I know I’m proud as hell of my city and our first responders. Real men protect. The first two pictures are of real men: Michael Collazo and Rex Englebert. Thank you 🙏

We have a severe mental health epidemic on our hands and it needs to be addressed honestly and accurately. Regardless of what side of the aisle we claim to fall on, good guys with guns protect against bad guys with guns - particularly in a place where guns are already illegal.

We DESPERATELY need armed security at every school. How is it even possible that every politician and hell Walmart has armed security …but we don’t have it around our children?!! What the actual f*ck. 

I’m angry. I’m shaken. My heart breaks for the families mourning loved ones gone way too soon. Innocent young lives and good people doing good. I’ve been in constant prayer for my city and staying in close proximity to my babies.

We’re all well aware of the truth and we need to start speaking it loudly and with confidence. This was a targeted terrorist attack. There is a severe ongoing mental health epidemic. Pretending it’s normal is not a solution.

#prayfornashville

Here’s to those weve loved.. I know they’re watching. 3 million plays and I’m still Missin You like crazy, Pap. 

I’m an independent artist.. so if my music touches you please share..let somebody know.. You never know if it might help them get through a real tough time 🕊️ 🦍
